### [Exodus Chapter 38](../../../bib/kjv/exo038.htm#001.md)

[Exodus](../../../bib/kjv/exo001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">exo 38:0</span></span>

INTRODUCTION TO EXODUS 38

This chapter is a continuation of the account of the making of the
things belonging to the tabernacle, particularly the altar of burnt
offering, [Exo 38:1](../../../bib/kjv/exo038.htm#001.md) the laver of
brass, and the things it was made of, [Exo
38:8](../../../bib/kjv/exo038.htm#008.md) the court and its hangings,
pillars, sockets, hooks and pins, [Exo
38:9](../../../bib/kjv/exo038.htm#009.md) then follows an account of the
quantities of gold, silver, and brass, expended in the making of the
several things appertaining to the sanctuary, [Exo
38:21](../../../bib/kjv/exo038.htm#021.md).

